        "MasterPrompt":  "Design a ‘4:5’ premium collectible postal-stamp poster for [Bo Sang, San Kamphaeng] blending modern philatelic design with handcrafted travel-art illustration and luxury minimalism. The poster should convey cultural pride, elegance, and destination identity through a giant postage stamp that fills the canvas edge-to-edge, framed like a national artifact.SUBJECT:A monumental vertical stamp dedicated to [BO SANG], illustrated in a refined handcrafted style—hybrid of gouache, silkscreen poster art, and premium editorial illustration.Capture the village’s defining atmosphere:traditional Lanna umbrella craftsmanship,hand-painted paper umbrellas,artisan workshops,wooden northern Thai houses,colorful umbrella streets,lantern festivals,bamboo structures,local markets,tropical greenery,and the calm cultural rhythm of San Kamphaeng.Avoid literal tourist clichés; simplify landmarks and cultural objects into elegant graphic forms.Perforation edges are large, tactile, and part of the visual identity.Surface should feel physically printed and collectible.COMPOSITION:The stamp itself is the full composition.Viewers enter via the oversized village name, then move through layered depth.Use asymmetric scenic flow with dominant elements rising diagonally — such as a giant painted umbrella canopy opening across the composition — while secondary forms wrap around naturally.Include intentional negative space for premium restraint.Thin elegant borders with subtle engraved linework and tiny postal marks.Perforation edges touch all sides for immersive, object-focused design.TYPOGRAPHY:Main text: [BO SANG] massive, integrated into the stamp, using elegant handcrafted serif typography inspired by vintage Southeast Asian travel ephemera and classic editorial design.Minimal additional text:tiny denomination,subtle “AIR MAIL” or “POST”,micro issue year,optional country line.Typography should feel printed, not digital.LIGHTING / PRINT:Luxury print-style lighting with soft highlights,tactile paper grain,embossed ink,subtle shadow around perforations.Focus on collectible realism.COLORS:Palette reflects [BO SANG, SAN KAMPHAENG] while remaining vibrant yet restrained.Use:saffron yellow,umbrella red,teak brown,soft turquoise,warm cream,muted emerald green.Balance one dominant color, one accent, and a neutral paper tone.Avoid random rainbow palettes.STYLE \u0026 FINISH:Handcrafted luxury illustration blended with modern editorial travel branding.Ultra-clean premium print finish:tactile texture,subtle embossing,refined ink,delicate edges.Feels collectible, museum-quality.FOOTER:Integrate a tiny engraved postal info strip into the bottom border with micro typography, serial numbers, and cancellation marks.NEGATIVE:Avoid generic travel posters,postcard clichés,floating landmarks,cluttered collages,excessive text,fake vintage distress,noisy textures,over-detailed realism,stock icons,random gradients,cheap souvenir aesthetics,basic centered layouts,or low-detail illustrations.",
