        "MasterPrompt":  "Cultural Craft Stamp Travel PosterTemplate Name: Cultural Craft Stamp Travel Poster{\"PROMPT\": \"Create a highly stylized illustrated travel poster based on [LOCATION_NAME], [CITY_OR_REGION], [COUNTRY].\",\"CORE GOAL\": \"- The final image must look like a collectible modern destination stamp poster.\\n- The artwork must celebrate the identity, [CULTURAL_HERITAGE_TYPE], [SPECIFIC_CRAFT_OR_TRADITION], [LOCAL_ARCHITECTURE], and artistic spirit of [LOCATION_NAME].\\n- The result must feel like a premium cultural travel poster suitable for tourism art, editorial design, or collectible postcard merchandise.\",\"MAIN COMPOSITION\": \"- Build one tall, dense, beautifully arranged poster composition centered around [LOCATION_NAME].\\n- Highlight iconic elements such as [ICONIC_CULTURAL_ELEMENTS], [TRADITIONAL_STRUCTURES], [ARTISAN_ACTIVITIES], [LOCAL_HOUSES], and [STREETSCAPE_FEATURES].\\n- Include cultural motifs like [SPECIFIC_PATTERNS], [DECORATIVE_OBJECTS], and [LOCAL_LIFE_SCENES].\\n- Layer these elements into a cohesive stacked composition with strong rhythm and elegant storytelling.\\n- The poster should feel rich and visually engaging while remaining clean and readable.\",\"VISUAL STYLE\": \"- flat graphic illustration\\n- poster design\\n- stamp-poster composition\\n- bold vector-like linework\\n- clean shape language\\n- layered cultural montage\\n- decorative editorial travel illustration\\n- modern collectible tourism graphic\\n- crisp and graphic, not photorealistic\",\"STAMP FRAME RULE\": \"- Surround the artwork with a postage-stamp style outer border.\\n- Use elegant scalloped perforation edges resembling a classic stamp.\\n- Ensure the frame integrates seamlessly with the poster design.\",\"TYPOGRAPHY RULE\": \"- \u0027[MAIN_TITLE]\u0027 must appear as the main large title near the top in bold elegant poster typography.\\n- Add a smaller supporting headline such as \u0027[SUB_HEADLINE]\u0027 above or near the title.\\n- Include a subtle [LOCAL_LANGUAGE] script accent such as \u0027[LOCAL_SCRIPT_TEXT]\u0027 in a refined placement.\\n- Add small decorative seal-like labels inspired by [IDENTITY_THEME].\\n- Typography must look premium, intentional, and editorial.\",\"AUTO CONTENT LOGIC\": \"- Emphasize [LOCATION_NAME] as a [PLACE_CHARACTER_TYPE] rather than a modern city.\\n- Include [SPECIFIC_WORKSHOPS], [PEOPLE_OR_ARTISANS], [ROWS_OF_OBJECTS], [STRUCTURAL_DETAILS], and [TRADITIONAL_LANDMARKS].\\n- Add local decorative elements such as [LOCAL_DECORATIONS], [NATURE_PATTERNS], and [HANDMADE_TEXTURES].\\n- Include environmental elements like [SKY_DETAILS], [LOCAL_FLORA], and [PATHWAY_TYPES].\\n- Convey a [ATMOSPHERE_MOOD] atmosphere.\",\"COLOR LOGIC\": \"- PRIMARY_COLOR: [COLOR_1]\\n- SECONDARY_COLOR: [COLOR_2]\\n- Use these two colors as the dominant palette.\\n- Allow tonal variations only (lighter/darker shades).\\n- Avoid introducing unrelated accent colors.\\n- Maintain a cohesive, bold, and branded visual identity.\",\"LAYOUT BEHAVIOR\": \"- The title at the top must be strong and dominant.\\n- The illustrated montage should fill most of the vertical space.\\n- Use overlapping [KEY_VISUAL_ELEMENTS_1], [KEY_VISUAL_ELEMENTS_2], [KEY_VISUAL_ELEMENTS_3], and decorative motifs to create depth.\\n- Maintain a clean, balanced, and intentional poster composition.\",\"DETAIL RULE\": \"- Include rich [LOCATION_SPECIFIC_DETAILS] such as [DETAIL_A], [DETAIL_B], and [DETAIL_C].\\n- Simplify all elements into a unified graphic illustration style.\\n- Maintain crisp edges and decorative clarity.\\n- Avoid photorealism.\",\"QUALITY TARGET\": \"- premium travel poster\\n- collectible stamp artwork\\n- clean graphic illustration\\n- rich cultural storytelling\\n- visually iconic\\n- editorial print quality\",\"NEGATIVE PROMPT\": \"photorealistic, messy collage, modern city skyline, generic landmarks, wrong architecture, too many colors, muddy composition, low-detail poster, bad typography, unrelated cultural symbols, cluttered realism, 3D render, watercolor, oil painting, blurry layout, weak graphic design, extra accent colors outside the two-color palette\"}",
