        "MasterPrompt":  "THEME: Heat Retention \u0026 Ergonomic Grip Flow (การเก็บความร้อนและรูปทรงจับถนัดมือของแก้วกาแฟ)FICTIONAL_BRAND_NAME: THERMOFORMFICTIONAL_PRODUCT_NAME: FLOWGRIP COFFEE CUP (แก้วกาแฟทรงโค้งรับสรีระและควบคุมอุณหภูมิ)FICTIONAL_SHORT_COPY: Hold the warmth. Shape the experience.ACCENT_COLORS: Matte Charcoal \u0026 Warm Coffee BrownTASK: Create a professional design concept and advertisement board presented in a single A4 vertical (portrait) composition, fusing a concept board, brand advertisement, and design development materials.[CORE VARIABLES]* THEME: {THEME}[AESTHETIC \u0026 STYLE]* Style: Minimal, poetic, intellectual composition. Beautifully balanced, generous white space. Pure seamless white background for easy cutouts.* Quality: High-resolution, precise, commercial visual quality.* Colors: Neutral base color palette (whites, grays), accented by 1–2 colors dynamically derived from the {THEME} (charcoal + warm brown accents).* Textures/Light: Precisely depict material textures such as ceramic, matte glaze, subtle steam condensation, and soft light reflections. Emphasize warmth, tactility, and curvature.[COMPOSITION - TWO-TIER SYSTEM]TIER 1: PROCESS DIAGRAM (Top Tier, ~40% of canvas)* Title: “MOTION TO FORM”. Clean, poetic typography at the top center.* Content: A professional process diagram visualizing the transformation of the {THEME} from concept to form in exactly 5 distinct stages, presented in a horizontal flow with delicate small arrows connecting them.* Stages (Strict Flow):    1. Source of Inspiration: Sketches of coffee cup silhouettes, hand grip studies, and heat zones. Label: “SOURCE OF INSPIRATION”.    2. Trajectory/Energy: Flow lines showing heat circulation and ergonomic grip paths. Label: “TRAJECTORY \u0026 ENERGY”.    3. Abstracted Lines/Structures: Geometric curves defining grip indentations and wall thickness variation. Label: “ABSTRACTED LINES \u0026 STRUCTURES”.    4. Three-Dimensional Form: 3D render showing cup curvature, handle integration, and thermal layering. Label: “THREE-DIMENSIONAL FORM”.    5. Completed Design: Final product render from multiple angles — top view and perspective — emphasizing form and usability. Label: “COMPLETED DESIGN”.* Formatting: Use delicate sketches, clean line diagrams, and refined render previews with center-aligned English labels and generous spacing.TIER 2: HERO VISUAL \u0026 ADVERTISEMENT (Bottom Tier, ~60% of canvas)* Content: A massive, dramatic, high-fidelity hero visual of the finalized coffee cup derived from the process above.* Object Selection (Resolved): Premium ergonomic coffee cup with integrated thermal design — sculpted grip surface, optimized wall thickness, and refined minimal handle or handle-less form.* Visual Direction:    * Slight perspective angle emphasizing curvature and depth    * Subtle steam rising from the cup    * Minimal coffee surface visible for realism    * Focus on material, warmth, and form* Advertising Elements:    * Brand Name: THERMOFORM (clean modern sans-serif)    * Product Name: FLOWGRIP COFFEE CUP    * Copy: “Hold the warmth. Shape the experience.”* FORMATTING: Arrange brand, product, and slogan with refined typography integrated into the lower composition. Maintain hierarchy and avoid clutter.[STRICT CONSTRAINTS]* Must be a single vertical A4 image (aspect ratio 3:4).* Strong visual continuity between Tier 1 diagram and Tier 2 product.* The product must feel real, manufacturable, and structurally logical.* Avoid excessive decoration, chaotic layout, or over-saturated visuals.* Maintain premium industrial design aesthetic.",
