        "MasterPrompt":  "THEME: Crispy Fried Bananas, Street Food Energy, Golden Crunch Textures, Tropical Market VibesBRAND_NAME: BANANA FRY FEST 2026INDUSTRY_SCENARIO: Street Food Festival \u0026 Cultural MarketPRIMARY_COLORS: Golden Yellow, Deep Banana Brown, Palm Leaf GreenSECONDARY_COLORS: Coconut White, Warm Orange, Charcoal BlackSTYLE_DIRECTION: Playful street-food pop, vibrant, slightly retro, fun and appetizing, Thai tropical market aestheticASPECT_RATIO: 16:9Please create a high-fidelity “Event Visual Identity Application Board” based on [Theme: {THEME}], [Brand Name / Event Name: {BRAND_NAME}], and [Industry / Scenario: {INDUSTRY_SCENARIO}].This is not a single poster, nor a simple logo design, but a comprehensive display of a brand visual system centered around the event theme. The visuals should resemble a professional design agency’s client proposal overview page, showcasing a complete extension of the event from main visuals, logos, IP characters, auxiliary graphics, to offline spatial materials, signage systems, peripheral stickers, and scene installations.[Overall Positioning]Design the [{BRAND_NAME}] into an event visual system with distinct recognizability, suitable for offline events, festival markets, brand pop-ups, commercial spaces, cultural tourism activities, or urban public events in the [{INDUSTRY_SCENARIO}] context.The overall design should convey a strong sense of branding, festivity, youthfulness, street-food culture, spatial implementation, and visual unity.[Aspect Ratio and Presentation]Aspect ratio: [{ASPECT_RATIO}].Present as a single brand visual system proposal board.Background suggestion: Pure white background color for easy cutouts, allowing different material modules to be clearly arranged like a portfolio showcase.The image should display multiple visual application modules of varying sizes and functions, rather than just one main visual.[Core Visual System]Establish a unified visual language around the [{THEME}], including:1. Main Logo / Main Title Design* Design a striking main title for the [{BRAND_NAME}].* The font should have a bold, chunky, crispy feel, inspired by fried batter textures, street signage, and Thai market typography.* Incorporate visual elements like banana slices, oil splashes, crunchy crumbs, or sizzling effects.* May include English subtitles, dates, locations, event slogans, and other auxiliary text.* The main logo should be adaptable for extension to various materials like storefronts, posters, stickers, signage boards, etc.2. Auxiliary Graphics System* Automatically generate a set of auxiliary graphic symbols based on the [{THEME}].* For example: banana shapes, crispy crumbs, oil bubbles, tropical leaves, stripes inspired by street stalls, price tags, hand-drawn icons.* All auxiliary graphics must align with the main visual and avoid becoming cluttered decorations.3. IP Characters / Mascots / Theme Figures* Design one or more cute, trendy, and shareable IP characters based on the [{THEME}].* Characters can be anthropomorphic fried bananas, smiling banana vendors, or playful food mascots holding skewers or baskets.* Characters should appear across different materials, such as storefronts, banners, stickers, signage boards, and check-in installations.* Character style should match the overall visual, friendly, appetizing, and highly recognizable.[Material Application Showcase]Display a complete set of event materials within the same image, including at least multiple modules from the following types:1. Large-scale main visual logo or entrance installation (e.g., giant fried banana archway)2. Event storefront / street food stall / check-in installation3. Booth header / pop-up stall / market stall inspired by Thai street vendors4. Pathway flags / hanging flags / banners with tropical food patterns5. Signage system (Entrance, Food Zone, Market, Rest Area, Parking, Toilet, etc.)6. Sticker system / social media stickers / food icons7. Floor signage / arrows shaped like banana slices8. Scene-based installations (food seating zone, tasting area, photo spot with oversized fried bananas)9. Peripheral materials (wristbands, food tickets, takeaway boxes, paper trays, cups, tote bags, badges)These materials should not exist in isolation but form a cohesive brand design system, embodying an extension relationship of “same theme, same colors, same graphic language, different application scenarios.”[Colors and Style]Primary colors: [{PRIMARY_COLORS}].Secondary colors: [{SECONDARY_COLORS}].Overall style: [{STYLE_DIRECTION}].Color requirements:High recognizability, strong contrast, appetizing and warm tones, suitable for food-related environments. Avoid dull or desaturated palettes. Maintain a unified brand identity.[Composition and Layout]Use a “multi-module brand system showcase board” composition approach.Do not create a single poster or just one logo.Suggested layout:* Top: Main logo + large fried banana entrance installation* Left: Flags, banners, and bold graphic patterns* Center: Food stalls, booths, signage systems* Right: IP characters, stickers, product packaging, installations* Bottom: Arrows, icons, functional signage, auxiliary graphicsMaintain clean spacing, hierarchy, and visual rhythm.Each module should look like a real, buildable event element.[Texture and Implementation Feel]Include realistic material textures such as:* Printed food packaging paper* Kraft paper trays* Fabric banners* Acrylic signage* Metal stall frames* Sticker cut edges* Street-market style boothsThe design should feel both illustrative and physically producible.[Text Handling]Include minimal but clear text such as:* [{BRAND_NAME}]* Location* Date* Event slogan (e.g., “Crispy. Sweet. Irresistible.”)* Functional signage (Entrance, Food Zone, Market, etc.)Text should integrate naturally into the design.If text rendering is unstable, prioritize layout and visual consistency.[Final Effect]The final image should resemble a professional agency-level event branding board, featuring:strong identity, cohesive visual system, rich application materials, lively street-food atmosphere, high commercial usability, and scalability for future events.Please avoid:Single poster output, isolated logo, inconsistent styles, cluttered visuals, lack of spatial applications, weak branding system, excessive text noise.",
        "ExampleImage":  "https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?authuser=0\u0026sz=w800\u0026id=1hIdn2wWs87-GRj1EJJ-oCFdr4aW3FqPm",
        "Application":  "• สำหรับครูผู้สอน: ใช้เป็นแผนภาพข้อมูล (Infographic) ประกอบการสอนเรื่องสัดส่วนสารอาหาร โภชนาการ หรือพืชสมุนไพรในท้องถิ่น และสามารถให้ผู้เรียนฝึกแปลงสูตรอาหารในครัวเรือนออกมาเป็นแผ่นภาพกราฟิกเพื่อฝึกทักษะการสื่อสารและการคิดเชิงระบบ (Systems Thinking)"
