        "MasterPrompt":  "THEME: Chiang MaiASPECT_RATIO: 3:4TASK: Create a highly collectible, designer-grade visual poster with high artistic authorship based on the [THEME]. Use the specified [ASPECT_RATIO].1. CORE AESTHETIC \u0026 STYLE* Style: Oil painting meets Master-level typography layout.* Texture: Prominent “Impasto” (thick paint) techniques. Use varying thicknesses to build 3D volume, material feel, rhythm, and visual hierarchy. Blend traditional painting textures with modern exhibition poster aesthetics, inspired by Lanna cultural richness.2. THE DIAGONAL BONE STRUCTURE (MAIN COMPOSITION)* Layout: Off-center, diagonal master layout.* The Core Visual: A massive, irregular “comprehensive color band / graphic zone” stretching from one diagonal corner to the opposite.* Flow: Expansive, atmospheric, and dominant — acting as the structural spine of the poster.* Dynamic Color Palette: Extract 2–3 dominant colors from Chiang Mai’s essence — e.g., Temple Gold, Forest Green, Misty Blue. Build a layered, atmospheric color relationship reflecting mountains, temples, and northern light.3. VISUAL SUBJECT GENERATION (EMBEDDED WITHIN THE DIAGONAL)* Auto-extract Chiang Mai core elements: Lanna temples (e.g., Doi Suthep silhouette), mountainous terrain, city moat geometry, lantern festivals (Yi Peng), traditional patterns.* Execution: Render as a minimalist bird’s-eye abstraction / topographic information landscape.* Integration: Seamlessly embed all elements along the diagonal color band, flowing continuously as one unified visual system. Avoid collage or literal realism.4. BACKGROUND \u0026 NEGATIVE SPACE* Canvas: Warm off-white / aged paper tone.* Texture: Subtle natural paper grain, premium print feel.* Restraint: Clean, calm, controlled.* Negative Space: Generous and intentional, emphasizing the diagonal structure and supporting typography placement.5. TYPOGRAPHY \u0026 HIERARCHY SYSTEM* Font Family: Serif-dominant (elegant, cultural, refined).* Hierarchy: Clear differentiation between main title, subtitles, and annotations using scale and spacing.* AVOIDANCE ROUTING (CRITICAL): Typography must NOT interrupt the diagonal visual band. Place text in surrounding negative space only.6. THE METALLIC TITLE (ENGLISH)* Title: “CHIANG MAI”* Material Finish: Premium metallic foil effect (e.g., antique gold or muted bronze-green reflecting Lanna heritage).* Placement: Positioned in negative space as a strong typographic anchor, interacting visually but never obstructing the diagonal flow.7. SURROUNDING KNOWLEDGE POINTS (ANNOTATIONS)* Include refined, minimal annotations such as:    * Coordinates of Chiang Mai    * Elevation / mountain references    * Cultural tags (Lanna, Yi Peng, Temple Architecture)    * Subtle geographic or historical markers* Layout: Elegantly distributed in clusters within the negative space, maintaining rhythm and clarity.8. SIGNATURE* Bottom right corner, very small, low-contrast font: “NAICHA DESIGN”9. STRICT NEGATIVE RESTRICTIONS (DO NOT VIOLATE)* NO breaking or interrupting the diagonal band with text.* NO cramped or cluttered layout.* NO tourist-style collage or literal imagery.* NO photorealism — must be thick-paint stylized.* NO cheap or overly shiny typography.* NO dense blocks of text or manual-style layout.",
