        "MasterPrompt":  "2x2 grid, do this for famous cities: Chiang Mai\u003cinstruction\u003e    1. Inference Engine (The Urban Topology):  Input A is a Major Cultural City: Chiang Mai, Thailand.  Deconstruct the city to generate 3 Papercraft Assets:       The Icons (The Landmarks): Identify 3–4 of the most famous, recognizable structures.           (e.g., Wat Phra That Doi Suthep, Wat Chedi Luang, Historic Chiang Mai Gate, Bo Sang Umbrella Village).       The Artery (The Road/River): Identify the primary mode of transport or defining waterway.           (e.g., Ping River, red songthaew trucks).       The Fabric (The Base Material): The entire construction is made from a specific type of recycled paper.           (e.g., Lanna-patterned saa paper, traditional mulberry paper with floral motifs, or vintage Thai manuscript paper).  2. Container (The Studio Void):    Goal: “Origami / Paper Diorama” Photography.    The Background: A clean, slightly crumpled, bright white Paper Studio Backdrop. It curves up behind the object seamlessly.    The Setting: The main sculpture floats in the center of the frame, disconnected from any real-world environment.3. The Impossible Geometry    The Form: The central structure is a massive, floating Twisted Ribbon or Mobius Strip.    The Roadway: The top, flat surface of this ribbon acts as a continuous highway or street, curving and looping over itself.    The Material: The sides and base of the ribbon are visibly constructed from folded and layered saa paper (The Fabric), featuring delicate Lanna patterns, fibrous textures, and subtle natural imperfections.4. The Diorama (The Pop-Up City):    The Skyline: The “Icons” (Step 1) and generic northern Thai buildings are placed along the edges of the twisting roadway.    Construction: They are 3D paper models, intricately folded from warm beige cardstock and patterned saa paper.    Physics: As the ribbon loops upside down, the buildings stick out sideways or hang from the bottom, defying gravity.    The Detail:    Tiny, solid-colored Paper Vehicles (e.g., red songthaews, small tuk-tuks) are glued to the roadway, driving along the twists.    A separate, folded piece of paper floats beneath the main loop. It features a strip of deep blue paper representing “The Artery” (Ping River), with tiny paper boats drifting along it.5. Lighting \u0026 Atmosphere:    Lighting: Soft Studio Product Lighting. Even, bright, and slightly warm to highlight the paper textures and cast gentle, clean shadows on the crumpled white background.    Texture: High fidelity. The viewer must clearly see the fibrous structure of saa paper, delicate Lanna patterns, crisp folds, and handcrafted imperfections of the paper art.    Color Direction: A more colorful version — incorporate warm gold, saffron orange, deep red, forest green, and sky blue accents inspired by Lanna culture and northern Thai festivals, while preserving the natural tones of the paper base.Output: ONE image, 1:1 Aspect Ratio, 3D Render/Photography, “Papercraft / Kirigami” aesthetic, High Macro Detail.",
