        "MasterPrompt":  "Create a detailed, highly engaging infographic-style travel guide for Chiang Mai (เชียงใหม่).The output should feel like a premium designer travel poster mixed with a fun comic illustration.Include:- A catchy title and short subtitle  Title: \"Chiang Mai – The Rose of the North\"  Subtitle: \"Mountains, Temples, Culture, and Slow Living Charm\"- What to see (specific places, not generic)  • Wat Phra That Doi Suthep (วัดพระธาตุดอยสุเทพ)  • Wat Chedi Luang (วัดเจดีย์หลวง)  • Wat Phra Singh (วัดพระสิงห์)  • Doi Inthanon National Park (อุทยานแห่งชาติดอยอินทนนท์)  • Mon Jam Viewpoint (ม่อนแจ่ม)  • Historic Chiang Mai Gate (ประตูท่าแพ)  • Baan Kang Wat Artist Village (บ้านข้างวัด)  • Ang Kaew Reservoir, Chiang Mai University (อ่างแก้ว มหาวิทยาลัยเชียงใหม่)- What to eat (local dishes, real names, correct Thai spelling)  • Khao Soi (ข้าวซอย)  • Sai Ua (ไส้อั่ว)  • Nam Prik Noom (น้ำพริกหนุ่ม)  • Nam Prik Ong (น้ำพริกอ่อง)  • Gaeng Hang Lay (แกงฮังเล)  • Khanom Jeen Nam Ngiao (ขนมจีนน้ำเงี้ยว)  • Sticky Rice (ข้าวเหนียว)  • Northern Thai sausage \u0026 grilled pork skewers (หมูปิ้ง / ไส้ย่าง)- What to do (mix of tourist + local + unique experiences)  • Join a Thai cooking class  • Visit an ethical elephant sanctuary  • Explore Sunday Walking Street (ถนนคนเดินวันอาทิตย์)  • Sip coffee in Nimmanhaemin (นิมมานเหมินทร์)  • Trekking in local hill tribe villages  • Experience a traditional Khantoke dinner (ขันโตก)  • Cycle around the Old City moat  - Local vibe (culture, behavior, atmosphere)  • Calm, friendly, and slow-paced lifestyle  • Strong Lanna cultural identity  • Respectful and polite social interactions  • Blend of traditional and modern café culture  • Early mornings and relaxed evenings  - Quick practical tips (transport, budget, mistakes to avoid)  • Transport: Use Grab, red trucks (รถแดง), or rent a motorbike  • Budget: Affordable compared to Bangkok, wide price range  • Best time: November–February (cool season)  • Avoid: Burning season haze (March–April)  • Dress modestly when visiting temples  • Carry cash for local markets  • Always negotiate politely in markets  Visual Style:Premium infographic poster, playful comic-style illustrations mixed with elegant layout, warm earthy tones (gold, green, terracotta), clean typography, icons for each section, subtle Lanna patterns.\nComposition:Balanced layout with clear sections, illustrated landmarks, food icons, character-style travelers, and strong visual hierarchy.Output:High-resolution, poster-ready, visually engaging, no watermark.",
