        "MasterPrompt":  "“A premium agency-level national identity system poster for Chiang Mai, vertical 2:3 format, dark sophisticated background, feels like a top Behance project from a world-class design studio.TOP SECTION: Large bold city name in premium editorial typography, short powerful regional statement underneath (max 5 words), 3-word identity descriptor (example: “Lanna / Serene / Timeless”)NATIONAL COLOR SYSTEM: Primary palette extracted directly from Lanna heritage, temple architecture, and northern landscapes — deep teak brown, gilded gold, forest green, misty mountain blue — large color blocks with hex codes, gradient combinations, light and dark mode applicationsCULTURAL TYPOGRAPHY: Headline font inspired by traditional Lanna scripts and temple inscriptions, show real phrases in Northern Thai (Lanna) language, clear typographic hierarchy from display to bodyVISUAL IDENTITY TILES: 5–6 cinematic image tiles showing the soul of Chiang Mai — mountain landscapes, northern cuisine, Lanna temples, local people, handicrafts, morning mist light. Editorial photography style. Each tile labeled with 3 descriptive wordsNATIONAL APPLICATIONS: Provincial identity applications including cultural passport-style booklet, regional airline livery inspired by northern motifs, tourism campaign billboard, travel ticket design, commemorative stamp series, traditional-inspired festival uniformPATTERN \u0026 MOTIF SYSTEM: Decorative patterns derived from Lanna art, temple carvings, traditional textiles, and natural elements such as mountains, clouds, and flowing water.”",
