        "MasterPrompt":  "A fun prompt for turning logos into brand worlds (Lanna Sky Lantern Edition).Use the uploaded business logo as the brand source of truth.First, analyze it and infer:(1) key geometric motifs,(2) 3–5 color palette swatches,(3) edge/line style (rounded vs sharp),(4) 3 brand adjectives, and(5) logo usage rules (no warping, clearspace, best placement).Then generate 4 images in a consistent style:low-poly 3D render + claymorphism + soft occlusion shadows, clean, minimal, warm, culturally refined, Northern Thai (Lanna) identity, Silicon Valley pitch deck quality, solid pastel purple background, aspect ratio 16:9.The logo must appear cleanly (as decal/signage/paint), never melted, never stretched, never re-drawn incorrectly. Keep the same brand palette across all 4.\nImage 1 — Hero Isometric / EstablishingA 3D isometric illustration of a floating Lanna lantern crafting village on a small island.The environment features:•Traditional wooden houses and bamboo structures•Artisans crafting โคมลอย (sky lanterns) by hand•Hanging lanterns glowing softly in warm light•Organized crafting zones (frame making, paper covering, drying area)•Gentle upward motion of a few lanterns being released into the skyMood: minimal, premium, serene, culturally rich, softly illuminated like twilight.Image 2 — Systems View / Ortho MapAn orthographic top-down “process map” of the same floating island.Clearly defined zones using abstract visual cues (no small text):•Bamboo frame preparation zone•Paper cutting \u0026 decorating zone•Assembly area•Drying / quality check zone•Launch platform for lantern releaseKeep materials consistent (wood, paper, bamboo, soft clay textures).Design should feel like a clean cultural workflow system, not industrial.Image 3 — Macro Detail / Close-UpClose-up cinematic shot of artisans’ hands assembling a lantern frame:•Thin bamboo strips being shaped into a circular structure•Soft paper texture being applied•Warm internal glow suggesting future ignitionBackground: softly blurred floating lanterns rising into the sky.Apply the logo as a crisp decal on a wooden tool box or work panel.Shallow depth of field, but maintain clarity and cleanliness.Image 4 — Brand Application MockA clean in-world mockup showing brand application on:•A lantern release platform signboard (wooden)•A transport crate or delivery cart used for lantern distributionStyle remains minimal, premium, and consistent with clay/low-poly aesthetic.The logo must be clearly visible, properly spaced, and elegantly integrated into the environment.If you want to push this further, I can extend it into a festival-scale world (ยี่เป็ง), or add storytelling layers for educational use such as integrating cultural meaning, sustainability, or STEM concepts into the visual system.",
