        "MasterPrompt":  "UNIVERSAL “MODULAR WOOD BLOCK RELIEF SYSTEM” PROMPT — CHIANG MAI EDITION  (IDENTITY LOCK – STRICT)Use Chiang Mai, Thailand as the primary subject and visual identity reference.IDENTITY LOCK – STRICT (NON-NEGOTIABLE)  Preserve the instantly recognizable identity of Chiang Mai:- Historic Chiang Mai Gate- Lanna architecture- temple silhouettes- old-town urban rhythm- mountain backdrop- lantern culture- Northern Thai street atmosphereDo not distort the cultural structure, architectural identity, or spatial recognizability of Chiang Mai.POSE \u0026 COMPOSITION – LOCKED  Keep the composition as a cinematic wide urban perspective of Chiang Mai Old Town.Maintain:- original city perspective- architectural proportions- skyline balance- street alignment- environmental layeringNo extreme camera distortion, mirroring, or surreal perspective shifts.STYLE TRANSFORMATION — WOOD BLOCK RELIEF (HARD)  Transform the entire Chiang Mai environment into a densely packed carved wood construction.Rebuild ALL forms using interlocking wooden structures:- temples- city walls- rooftops- lanterns- trees- roads- mountains- markets- vehicles- people- signageEverything must be reconstructed from:- carved wooden blocks- stacked timber beams- cylindrical dowels- sliced wood cross-sections- layered planks- carved architectural fragmentsMaintain extremely high packing density with almost no empty flat areas.MATERIAL SYSTEM — WOOD (CRITICAL)  All elements must be realistic natural wood:- teak wood- aged Lanna timber- warm cedar tones- carved hardwood texturesVisible details must include:- wood grain direction- growth rings- carved knife marks- cut ends- knots- subtle imperfections- natural tonal variationGrain direction should follow architectural and environmental form naturally.Finish:matte to semi-matte natural wood only.No plastic.No glossy CGI surfaces.DEPTH \u0026 STRUCTURE — HARD RELIEF  Construct the entire Chiang Mai scene as a monumental carved relief wall.Use:- layered depth stacking- overlapping timber geometry- stepped architectural carving- interlocking wooden city structuresForeground, midground, and background must clearly separate through carved relief depth.Historic Chiang Mai Gate, temple roofs, and old-town streets should emerge dramatically from the layered wooden structure.ARCHITECTURE \u0026 ENVIRONMENT INTEGRATION — UNIFIED SYSTEM (CRITICAL)  All Chiang Mai cultural elements must belong to the same carved wood system.Examples:- temple roofs become layered carved planks- lanterns become rounded carved wood forms- trees become stacked timber clusters- clouds become flowing carved wood grain waves- mountains become massive sculpted timber reliefsNothing should feel like a separate material.Everything is wood.LIGHTING — FORM REVEAL  Use strong directional lighting to emphasize:- carved depth- relief layering- edge separation- wood grain texture- architectural rhythmLighting should create dramatic shadows that reveal the sculptural complexity of Chiang Mai’s carved wooden cityscape.MOOD \u0026 AESTHETIC  The final image should feel:- handcrafted- monumental- culturally rich- architectural- tactile- museum-scale- artisan-built- spiritually connected to Northern Thai craftsmanshipThe atmosphere should resemble:an enormous carved Lanna wooden mural reconstructed through modular timber engineering.NEGATIVE PROMPT (STRICT)  No smooth painted surfaces.No realistic concrete.No plastic.No metal.No soft airbrush blending.No empty negative spaces.No low-detail geometry.No floating abstract pieces.No glossy CGI look.No distortion of Chiang Mai architecture.No random modern sci-fi structures.No photobashed textures.Everything must remain:densely carved,structurally interlocked,fully wooden,and culturally recognizable as Chiang Mai.",
