        "MasterPrompt":  "Some cities become cinema at sunset.Now you can turn your own city into one too.I wanted to capture that exact feeling through prompts — quiet golden light, reflective rice terraces, slow mountain atmosphere, and the emotional stillness of a final movie scene.GPT Image 2 on ChatGPTCreate a premium cinematic destination travel poster for Mae Chaem, Chiang Mai in the same emotional tone and visual atmosphere as a nostalgic mid-century travel illustration blended with modern editorial serenity.The image must center around ONE instantly recognizable landmark or iconic scenic location that emotionally defines Mae Chaem — such as the terraced rice fields of Ban Pa Pong Piang, mist-covered mountain valleys, or a peaceful northern Thai countryside road winding through layered hills.The composition should capture a quiet, intimate “moment of time” unfolding naturally around the landscape — for example: farmers walking slowly through glowing rice terraces at sunset, drifting mist over mountain ridges, lantern light from wooden Lanna houses, water buffalo near reflective paddies, or villagers quietly cycling along narrow rural roads. The mood should feel calm, romantic, nostalgic, and deeply atmospheric rather than busy or touristic.VERY IMPORTANT:The landscape and cultural atmosphere must remain visually authentic and immediately recognizable as Northern Thailand. Avoid fantasy redesigns or exaggerated sci-fi reinterpretations. The image should feel like an idealized memory of a real place. Prioritize emotional travel nostalgia, peaceful rural life, and cinematic stillness. Tiny human figures, farmers, cyclists, children, monks, or villagers may appear to reinforce scale and warmth, but the landscape and surrounding atmosphere remain the emotional focus.STYLE:dreamy cinematic travel poster,retro-modern editorial illustration,soft painterly realism,refined atmospheric perspective,subtle grain,elegant simplification,premium tourism-poster aesthetics,emotionally warm composition,quiet luxury travel mood,nostalgic visual storytelling,timeless destination identity,peaceful environmental storytelling.COLOR \u0026 LIGHTING:soft sunset palette inspired by Northern Thailand,golden rice tones,misty sage green mountains,warm teak brown,soft indigo shadows,pastel peach sky gradients,warm reflected evening light,gentle atmospheric haze,long shadows,soft glowing sunlight,subtle mountain mist,cinematic rim lighting,muted but rich earthy colors,elegant tonal harmony.Avoid oversaturated neon colors.COMPOSITION:vertical 4:5 poster composition,large breathing space,strong foreground-midground-background layering,the terraced landscape positioned prominently but integrated naturally into the environment,wide calm sky area,reflective rice paddies and mountain atmosphere,balanced negative space,cinematic depth.Include small environmental motion such as drifting fog, birds, wind-blown rice plants, floating lanterns, distant smoke from village chimneys, or ripples in water terraces to create gentle life and movement.TEXT:place the destination name “MAE CHAEM” in large elegant sans-serif typography near the bottom area, integrated naturally into the composition like a premium tourism campaign poster.Typography should feel clean, minimal, timeless, and internationally recognizable.QUALITY:ultra high resolution,premium print-ready poster aesthetic,refined painterly detail,cinematic realism blended with editorial illustration,emotionally immersive atmosphere,iconic Northern Thailand storytelling,globally appealing tourism campaign visual identity.",
