        "MasterPrompt":  "[HOD DISTRICT, CHIANG MAI, THAILAND] minimalist urban travel sketch poster, drawn like a real location sketch captured by an experienced urban sketch artist during quiet morning travel moments.Before drawing, carefully analyze and express the authentic visual identity and emotional rhythm of the district:its low-rise roadside architecture,northern Thai rural-town atmosphere,mountain backdrop,local transportation culture,slow walking rhythm,traditional storefronts,warm earthy color palette,soft hazy sunlight,and gentle everyday movement of local people.Style:refined on-location urban sketching,expressive pen-and-ink drawing combined with transparent watercolor washes,delicate but confident black ink linework,varied line weight,slightly imperfect hand-drawn perspective,quick observational sketch strokes,broken contour lines,subtle architectural drafting details,visible sketch construction marks,organic hand pressure variation,authentic travel sketchbook feeling.Watercolor treatment:transparent watercolor layering,soft watercolor blooming,gentle pigment granulation,wet-on-wet diffusion,accidental watercolor bleeding,subtle paper absorption texture,light watercolor stains,soft atmospheric washes,preserved white paper highlights,minimal but emotionally rich color palette.Paper:clean white premium sketchbook paper,subtle cotton paper grain,slightly textured watercolor paper surface,visible dry brush friction,natural sketchbook breathing space.Composition:calm editorial travel poster layout,asymmetrical visual balance,large negative space,airy and elegant composition,human-scale street perspective,foreground-middle-background depth,natural eye-flow through the street scene,quiet cinematic framing.Scene:show an authentic everyday moment of Hot District,not a tourist postcard.Include subtle local urban and rural elements naturally integrated into the environment:small roadside coffee shops,wooden market stalls,northern Thai shop signs,motorcycles parked beside old buildings,pickup trucks and red songthaew transportation,crosswalks,street trees,banana plants,weathered concrete textures,electrical wires,students in uniforms,local vendors,temple walls,quiet morning movement,and distant mountain silhouettes inspired by Doi Tao and the surrounding highlands.Mood:warm,poetic,observational,calm,sophisticated,nostalgic yet modern,like a beautifully remembered travel diary page.Lighting:soft natural morning or late afternoon light,gentle watercolor shadows,atmospheric air perspective,subtle reflected light,slightly cool-season northern Thailand atmosphere,quiet dry-season mood.Typography:elegant minimalist typography integrated softly into the composition:“HOD DISTRICT”“Everyday Northern Rhythm”Avoid:tourist postcard aesthetics,over-rendered digital illustration,heavy outlines,oversaturated colors,crowded composition,vector-like precision,perfect perspective,AI-generated hyper-detail feeling.Rendering:ultra-high-resolution,premium urban sketchbook aesthetic,realistic pen pressure texture,authentic watercolor transparency,luxury travel journal illustration feeling,subtle northern Thai cultural atmosphere,editorial-quality handcrafted travel artwork.",
