        "MasterPrompt":  ".USER INPUTS:* LOCATION_NAME: Nan Heritage District, Thailand* CENTRAL_LANDMARKS: Wat Phumin, Wat Phra That Khao Noi, Nan National Museum, Kuang Mueng Nan Walking Street* COLOR_PALETTE: Lanna Gold, Teak Brown, Rice Cream, Forest Green* TRANSPORT_ELEMENTS: Traditional Samlor trishaws, Vintage bicycles, Local songthaew trucks* LANGUAGE_MODE: BILINGUAL (Thai/English)TASK: Generate a high-fidelity, illustrated isometric map of [LOCATION_NAME].[1. VISUAL DNA \u0026 STYLE]* Perspective: Slightly isometric top-down oblique view (Modern Diorama style).* Art Style: High-end flat vector illustration with clean, uniform line weights.* Influences: A hybrid of contemporary editorial city maps, minimalist travel infographics, and modern flat design.* Line Work: Precise, sharp outlines with consistent thickness. Flat color fills with subtle, translucent drop shadows to create clean depth layers.[2. GEOGRAPHIC ARCHITECTURE]* Landmass: Depict the area as a dense, vibrant [LOCATION_NAME] landmass.* Water System: Surround the area with the Nan River boundary. Use a clean [COLOR_PALETTE] for water, featuring minimalist stylized ripples to represent currents and fluid motion.* Urban Grid: Roads and pathways should be rendered using a clear color hierarchy from [COLOR_PALETTE], creating an organized and readable visual “circulatory system” for the city.[3. LANDMARK \u0026 DETAIL LOGIC]* Primary Landmarks: Illustrate [CENTRAL_LANDMARKS] with high precision, capturing the traditional Northern Thai Lanna architectural style. Focus on iconic silhouettes, multi-tier temple rooflines, naga staircases, teakwood structures, and unique mural-inspired ornaments.* Urban Density: Fill the interior blocks with region-specific building types such as traditional wooden shophouses, Lanna-style homes, artisan cafés, and local market buildings that match the local aesthetic of [LOCATION_NAME].* Vegetation: Scatter stylized circular tree canopies in shades of forest green and seasonal tropical colors, ensuring they are placed naturally near temples, parks, and riverside zones.[4. MAP ORNAMENTATION \u0026 TEXT]* Typography: Render all labels strictly in [LANGUAGE_MODE]. Use small, clean call-out boxes for street names and fluid, curved text following the river paths.* Compass Rose: Include a minimalist or traditional Lanna-inspired compass rose in the corner, with cardinal directions clearly labeled in Thai and English.* Narrative Elements: Add [TRANSPORT_ELEMENTS] in relevant areas to add movement and regional Northern Thai context.* Attribution: Place a clean, minimalist credit text at the bottom: “Illustrated Cultural Map of Nan, Thailand”.[5. TECHNICAL QUALITY \u0026 MOOD]* Atmosphere: Peaceful, cultural, artisan, and timeless Northern Thai heritage atmosphere.* Quality: Masterpiece, 8k resolution, sharp vector edges, print-ready clarity.* Layout: Adaptive/Auto orientation based on the natural geographical shape of the area.* Restrictions: NO 3D photorealism, NO messy or overlapping labels, NO realistic human faces. Maintain a clean, premium editorial aesthetic.",
