        "MasterPrompt":  "[MASTER PROMPT — CINEMATIC HERITAGE POSTER (PHOTOGRAPHIC)]TASK: Create a professional, epic, master-class photographic movie poster campaign based on the Thai literary epic Phra Aphai Mani. The visual quality must look like genuine, raw 35mm film photography, not a 3D rendering.VISUAL COMPOSITION (THE PHOTOGRAPHIC BLEND LOGIC)* Composition: A massive, highly photographic side profile (medium close-up) of Phra Aphai Mani dominates the left side. He is portrayed as a noble, contemplative figure holding a traditional flute near his lips, gazing toward the horizon. The entire composition must follow LAYOUT_STYLE.* Double Exposure Logic: Artistically integrate key supporting characters within the internal shadow areas of his profile using a seamless photographic double-exposure effect:    * The mermaid (นางเงือก) guiding him across the ocean    * The sea ogress (ผีเสื้อสมุทร) emerging with emotional intensity    * Sudsakorn (สุดสาคร) riding a mythical horse across waves        These elements must blend naturally into the shadow contours—no hard edges or graphic cutouts.* Background: A sprawling, atmospheric oceanic mythological landscape, featuring rolling sea waves, distant islands, traditional sailing boats, seabirds in motion, and glowing golden clouds near the horizon. The environment should evoke a sense of epic journey, destiny, and poetic fantasy grounded in realism.LIGHTING \u0026 COLOR (ANALOG GOLDEN HOUR)* Lighting: Warm, masterful natural Golden Hour sunset lighting. Soft natural bokeh across the sea surface, with deep, legible dynamic range. Use subtle rim lighting along the subject’s silhouette and supporting figures to enhance separation and depth.* Color Palette: Follow TONE_AND_MOOD — rich ambers, deep oranges, earthy browns, muted ocean blues, and soft teal undertones to create a nostalgic, refined cinematic tone.* Texture (CRITICAL): Visible natural 35mm film grain, slight color shift, dust particles in the air, and tactile fabric textures. The image must feel organic and archival, not digitally perfect.AUTHENTIC HUMAN DETAILS (RAW PHOTOGRAPHY)* Appearance: Characters must exhibit 100% realistic human features — visible pores, fine facial hair, natural skin texture, slight imperfections, and authentic bone structure. No artificial smoothing or CG-like rendering.* Attire: Traditional Thai literary-inspired costumes:    * Phra Aphai Mani in royal poetic attire with flowing fabric    * Mermaid with natural aquatic textures and subtle realism    * Sea ogress with grounded, believable physical presence (not exaggerated fantasy CGI)        Fabrics must show real weave, weight, aging, and environmental interaction.* Expressions: Deeply emotional, introspective, and cinematic — conveying longing, fate, love, and inner conflict.POSTER TYPOGRAPHY (CLEAN \u0026 ELEGANT)* Concept: All text must appear as a refined graphic overlay (not embedded in the physical environment).* Title Placement: Centered or slightly off-center at the bottom-third.* Title Font: Render the main title in Thai:    “พระอภัยมณี”    Use a graceful, flowing Thai cursive or elegant serif style with perfect spelling and high readability.* Credit Block: Include SUB_TEXT and a minimalist “Movie Credit Block” (actors, director, production) in very small, clean sans-serif font at the bottom, following an Apple-style editorial layout.STRICT ARTISTIC RESTRICTIONS* STRICTLY NO messy or AI-gibberish text* NO vibrant or neon colors* NO 3D-render look, NO overly smooth digital skin, NO plastic-like textures* NO oversaturation* NO artificial CG-style hair or lighting* NO watermarks or random signaturesCreative Direction:This poster must feel like a lost cinematic masterpiece — blending Thai literary heritage with world-class photographic storytelling. The tone should be poetic, timeless, and emotionally resonant, grounded in realism while honoring myth and imagination.",
