        "Recipe":  "• เนื้อหา/เป้าหมายบทเรียน [SUBJECT]: เครื่องจักร กลไกทางวิศวกรรม หรือโครงสร้างทางชีวภาพ   • รูปแบบและสไตล์ศิลปะ [STYLE]: Patent Drawing / Vector Drafting Lines with Cross-hatching   • โครงสร้างการจัดวาง [LAYOUT]: Exploded-view with floating layers and XML specification tags",
        "MasterPrompt":  "\u003ctechnical_spec\u003e      STYLE: 19th–20th century Patent Drawing / Technical Blueprint.      FORMAT: 2×2 grid, each quadrant = one FIGURE (FIG.1–FIG.4).      COLOR: Cyanotype Blue OR Monochrome Black Ink.      LINEWORK: Precision vector drafting lines; cross-hatching for shading; stipple for material density.      LABELING: Engineering callouts, figure titles, part numbers, dotted leader lines.      CAMERA: Orthographic projection (no perspective distortion).  \u003c/technical_spec\u003e  \u003clayer_logic\u003e      * Layer 1: OUTER SHELL        (red painted body panels, roof canopy, rear step platform, side openings, windshield, doors or open cabin structure)    * Layer 2: STRUCTURAL FRAME        (pickup truck chassis, steel frame, passenger bench supports, roof pillars, suspension mounting points)    * Layer 3: FUNCTIONAL SYSTEMS        (engine, drivetrain, transmission, steering system, braking system, fuel tank, cooling system)    * Layer 4: MICRO-COMPONENTS        (wiring harness, lighting circuits, fasteners, seat fixtures, handrails, signal systems, small mechanical joints)    * Each layer floats apart in Z-space with consistent spacing.      * Maintain real-world mechanical plausibility and routing logic for a converted shared taxi vehicle.  \u003c/layer_logic\u003e  \u003ctransformation\u003e      * Convert the vehicle into a ghosted exploded-view with transparent outer layers.      * Add callout numbers + concise engineering labels (e.g., “Passenger Bench Assembly,” “Roof Canopy Frame,” “Rear Access Step”).      * Add FIGURE TITLES per quadrant:          FIG.1 — External Form \u0026 Shell          FIG.2 — Structural Framework          FIG.3 — Functional Mechanisms          FIG.4 — Micro-Components \u0026 Internal Routing      * Preserve instructional clarity, drafting precision, and patent-sheet readability.      * No stylization beyond blueprint/patent conventions.  \u003c/transformation\u003e  Output: one image",
