        "Recipe":  "• เนื้อหา/เป้าหมายบทเรียน [SUBJECT]: หัวข้อบทเรียนหรือชุดข้อมูลเปรียบเทียบ 4 มิติ   • รูปแบบและสไตล์ศิลปะ [STYLE]: High Detail Readability / Polished Concept Sheet   • โครงสร้างการจัดวาง [LAYOUT]: Multi-panel Grid Layout with clear typography",
        "MasterPrompt":  "Search the web for detailed information about Ton Pao Subdistrict, San Kamphaeng District, Chiang Mai, Thailand — including its history, local identity, umbrella-making heritage, handicraft culture, community economy, temples, architecture, transportation routes, markets, traditional lifestyle, and surprising lesser-known details.Then create a dramatic editorial infographic poster about Ton Pao Subdistrict in the style of a National Geographic environmental and cultural feature — but focused on local craft culture, roadside urbanism, and Northern Thai identity.CORE VISUAL CONCEPT:Ton Pao becomes the full-bleed atmospheric hero of the composition:* a photorealistic cinematic render combining San Kamphaeng roadside atmosphere, umbrella handicraft workshops, traditional Northern Thai shophouses, local cafés, market life, utility wires, temples, artisan activity, and warm evening light* the environment fills the entire poster from top to bottom* layered urban depth with storefronts, hanging umbrellas, local signage, passing motorbikes, pickup trucks, and Chiang Mai suburban atmosphere* dramatic natural lighting inspired by real Northern Thailand golden hour and rainy-season humidity* no empty background areasEDITORIAL OVERLAY SYSTEM:* Text and infographic overlays float organically over the environment like premium National Geographic editorial spreads* No rigid magazine grid* No boxed infographic layout* Information layers should feel naturally integrated into the streetscape* Use semi-transparent earthy-red, bamboo-beige, lacquer-brown, and warm charcoal panels inspired by Ton Pao’s craft cultureTYPOGRAPHY:* Oversized bold typography dominates the upper portion:“TON PAO”* Subtitle below:    “ตำบลต้นเปา • สันกำแพง • เชียงใหม่ • THAILAND”* Typography style:    bold editorial serif mixed with elegant modern sans-serif,    luxury documentary aesthetic,    high readability,    cinematic placement integrated into the urban environmentMAIN ENVIRONMENT HERO:* Ton Pao roadside district atmosphere as the visual anchor* Include:    * traditional umbrella craft workshops    * hand-painted Bo Sang-style umbrellas    * Northern Thai roadside architecture    * artisan storefronts    * local cafés and noodle shops    * temple rooftops    * electrical poles and dense utility wires    * market activity    * bicycles, motorbikes, and pickup trucks    * warm humid Chiang Mai suburban ambiance* Everything should feel naturally connected rather than collage-likeANNOTATED CALLOUTS:Add elegant editorial callout lines pointing directly toward:* umbrella-painting workshops* bamboo framework structures* hand-painted umbrella motifs* traditional Northern Thai architecture* local markets* roadside artisan culture* temple ornament detailsFLOATING DATA PANELS:Use layered infographic overlays covering:* Ton Pao historical background* San Kamphaeng handicraft heritage* umbrella-making industry significance* population and community economy* cultural tourism importance* transportation connections to Chiang Mai city* local artisan production* 3 surprising lesser-known facts about Ton PaoSURPRISING FACTS SECTION:Include visually integrated editorial facts such as:* Ton Pao’s connection to the famous umbrella-making tradition of San Kamphaeng* handcrafted umbrella production techniques passed through generations* the role of artisan communities in Chiang Mai cultural tourism* hidden local cafés and roadside creative spaces* integration of traditional craft culture with modern suburban Chiang Mai lifeMAP \u0026 INFOGRAPHIC ELEMENTS:* small inset map showing Ton Pao within San Kamphaeng District and Chiang Mai Province* icon-based stats row including:    * handicraft production    * tourism    * local economy    * artisan workshops    * temple culture    * transportation access* subtle Northern Thai ornamental line graphics blended into the compositionPULL QUOTE:Include one bold editorial pull quote integrated into the environment:“Where Chiang Mai craftsmanship still lives on every street.”COLOR SYSTEM:The entire palette must be extracted naturally from Ton Pao itself:* umbrella red* lacquer brown* bamboo beige* warm concrete grey* rainy-season green* faded signage cream* muted terracotta* humid golden-hour amberLIGHTING \u0026 MOOD:cinematic but realistic,warm Northern Thai evening atmosphere,humid roadside ambience,National Geographic documentary realism,immersive environmental storytelling,dense tactile realism,rich artisan-community moodSTYLE:photorealistic editorial infographic,National Geographic-inspired cultural + urban feature,luxury travel-documentary poster,cinematic environmental realism,organic layered infographic design,dense but readable information hierarchy,premium publication-quality compositionRESTRICTIONS:* no white background* no clean corporate infographic grid* no flat vector infographic style* no isolated panels* no cartoon look* no sci-fi aesthetics* no generic tourism brochure layout* no empty negative space* no simplistic renderingOUTPUT:* single vertical 4:5 poster* ultra-high-resolution* dense cinematic editorial composition* print-ready* tactile layered infographic realism* full-bleed environmental storytelling aestic:::",
        "ExampleImage":  "https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?authuser=0\u0026sz=w800\u0026id=1DgJX8w1ns-_1I4c9BP3pzC1JiTJLy03E",
        "Application":  "• สำหรับครูผู้สอน: นำภาพผลลัพธ์ไปประยุกต์ใช้เป็น สื่อกระตุ้นการคิด (Thinking Tools) สื่อประกอบการสอนแบบตั้งคำถาม (Inquiry-based Learning) นำแผ่นภาพโครงสร้างไปทำโมเดลกระดาษสามมิติ หรือทำการ์ดกิจกรรมประกอบแอปพลิเคชันการจัดทำแผนการสอนเพื่อพัฒนาทักษะการวิเคราะห์เชิงลึกของผู้เรียน   • สำหรับผู้บริหาร: ใช้เป็นแนวทางต้นแบบในการส่งเสริมให้ครูผู้สอนพัฒนาสื่อนวัตกรรมการเรียนรู้ที่ทันสมัย สอดคล้องกับแนวคิดนวัตกรรมการศึกษา (Learning Innovation) และสามารถนำสไตล์การจัดสรุปข้อมูล (เช่น โครงสร้าง Infographic หรือพิมพ์เขียว) ไปใช้จัดทำแผนภาพยุทธศาสตร์การพัฒนาคุณภาพของโรงเรียนเพื่อนำเสนอต่อผู้ทรงคุณวุฒิหรือหน่วยงานต้นสังกัด"
