        "Recipe":  "• เนื้อหา/เป้าหมายบทเรียน [SUBJECT]: ขั้นตอนการทดลอง วัฏจักรธรรมชาติ หรือสรุปเนื้อหาบทเรียน   • รูปแบบและสไตล์ศิลปะ [STYLE]: Modern Editorial / Clean Minimal Vector Icons   • โครงสร้างการจัดวาง [LAYOUT]: Structured Layout with numbered panels and stats badges",
        "MasterPrompt":  "Create a professional educational infographic worksheet for Social Studies / Local History class on the topic “Ping River, Chiang Mai” for upper elementary / lower secondary students. The worksheet should be designed in a modern, visually engaging educational infographic style with vibrant colors, clean typography, and highly readable layouts that encourage Historical Thinking, Geographical Thinking, and Environmental Thinking skills.The worksheet must emphasize:* Inquiry-Based Learning* Active Learning* Critical Thinking* Future ThinkingThe learning experience should encourage students to:* investigate geographical and historical evidence* observe and analyze river ecosystems and local communities* connect causes and effects between humans and nature* compare the past and present condition of the Ping River* predict possible future environmental and community changesThe focus should NOT be rote memorization, but meaningful understanding of local history, geography, environment, and sustainable development.MAIN TITLE:“Educational Worksheet : Ping River, Chiang Mai”Include:* student name section* class* number* dateVISUAL STYLE:* modern educational infographic worksheet* contemporary museum-exhibition aesthetic* premium Thai educational media design* visually organized section cards* clean and colorful educational layout* Pixar-inspired educational atmosphere* highly engaging but academically professionalCOLOR PALETTE:Use nature-inspired Northern Thai colors:* river blue* emerald green* warm gold* teak brown* soft sky blue* contemporary Thai pastel accentsGRAPHIC ELEMENTS:Include educational icons and visuals such as:* maps of Chiang Mai and the Ping River* bridges and riverside communities* traditional Lanna boats* temples along the river* fish and river ecosystems* magnifying glass* timeline graphics* comparison charts* environmental and cultural symbolsCHARACTER ELEMENT:Include a friendly educational guide character:“Krucopter” or a young river explorer guidein a cute 3D Pixar-style educational character design.LAYOUT STRUCTURE:Vertical A4 printable layoutClear section hierarchyReadable Thai/English educational typographyHigh-resolution printable qualityPremium classroom exhibition designAdd the educational slogan:“Learn from the River, Understand the Community, Design a Sustainable Future.”The worksheet should contain 7 clearly separated sections with elegant infographic-style cards.SECTION 1 — LEARNING OBJECTIVESStudents should be able to:* explain the importance of the Ping River to Chiang Mai* analyze how rivers influence communities and culture* study environmental and historical changes of the river* connect river ecosystems with modern urban life* predict future environmental impacts and conservation solutionsSECTION 2 — PART A : INQUIRY STARTERCreate a local inquiry activity with guiding questions such as:“Why did ancient communities choose to settle near the Ping River?”“How would life in Chiang Mai change if the Ping River disappeared?”Include:* river map illustrations* observation visuals* exploration spaceAdd a thinking table:“What I Observe”“What I Wonder”“What I Predict”Encourage curiosity and evidence-based thinking.SECTION 3 — PART B : RIVER TIMELINE EXPLORERCreate a large infographic timeline including major developments such as:* early Lanna settlements near the river* river transportation and trade* agricultural development* modern urban expansion along the Ping River* environmental conservation projectsActivities:* fill in missing historical/environmental events* arrange events chronologically* analyze which development changed the river most and explain whyInclude:* timeline graphics* environmental icons* arrows and visual flowSECTION 4 — PART C : CAUSE \u0026 EFFECT ANALYSISCreate a thinking chart with columns:“Event or Change”“Cause”“Effect”“What if this never happened?”Example topics:* urban expansion* flooding* deforestation upstream* tourism growth* river conservation projectsStrong emphasis on:Cause-and-Effect ThinkingEnvironmental reasoningCritical analysisSECTION 5 — PART D : PAST VS PRESENTCompare:“Ping River in the Past” vs “Ping River Today”Comparison topics:* transportation* water quality* riverside communities* environment* agriculture* tourism and economyUse:* Venn Diagram* comparison chart* infographic comparison visualsEncourage students to identify continuity and change over time.SECTION 6 — PART E : FUTURE RIVER DESIGNEREncourage Future Thinking activities such as:“If pollution in the Ping River continues, what might Chiang Mai look like in the future?”“How should communities protect and develop the Ping River sustainably over the next 50 years?”Provide writing space for:* creative environmental proposals* future city ideas* conservation plans* sustainable community conceptsSECTION 7 — REFLECTIONReflection prompts:“Today I discovered that…”“The most important role of the Ping River is…”“A lesson from the Ping River that can help the future is…”Include self-assessment checkboxes for:* investigation skills* analytical thinking* environmental awareness* comparison skills* future prediction skills* teamwork and participationIMAGE \u0026 DESIGN DETAILS:* printable 4K quality* vertical A4 composition* modern classroom infographic design* Pixar-inspired environmental classroom aesthetic* realistic educational poster quality* premium Thai teaching-media appearance* organized but visually exciting* balanced use of whitespace and infographic densityIMPORTANT DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:* prioritize questioning over memorization* encourage exploration and environmental reasoning* visually beautiful and highly organized* stimulate curiosity and active participation* feel like a professional teacher-created educational exhibition worksheet",
