        "MasterPrompt":  "[USER INPUT]CITY: Koh Luang Waterfall, Li DistrictCOUNTRY: ThailandLANDMARK_OR_LOCAL_IDENTITY: The crystal-clear turquoise limestone waterfall terraces of Koh Luang Waterfall surrounded by dense Northern Thai forest, bamboo groves, moss-covered rocks, and peaceful tropical mountain scenery in Lamphun Province.MAIN_SCENE_TYPE: WATERFALL LANDSCAPEMOOD: PEACEFULTYPOGRAPHY_LANGUAGE: BILINGUAL[PROMPT]Create a full-bleed architectural travel illustration inspired by [CITY], [COUNTRY], in a soft hand-drawn watercolor and ink style.[CORE GOAL]- Create an editorial travel illustration that captures the visual identity and atmosphere of [CITY], [COUNTRY].- Use [MAIN_SCENE_TYPE] as the main visual subject.- Incorporate [LANDMARK_OR_LOCAL_IDENTITY] naturally into the scene so the image feels clearly connected to the city.- The local identity element may appear in the architecture, background, skyline, street details, landscape, signage, materials, patterns, or surrounding scenery.- Keep the overall image elegant, locally rooted, and suitable for a refined destination artwork.[STYLE]- Delicate hand-drawn architectural illustration- Soft watercolor washes- Thin ink outlines- Slightly imperfect sketch lines- Gentle handmade texture- Subtle watercolor grain within the artwork- Editorial travel illustration aesthetic- Calm and refined visual tone- No photorealism- No harsh contrast- No overly saturated colors- No dramatic cinematic lighting[SCENE]- Show a locally inspired architectural or environmental scene based on [MAIN_SCENE_TYPE].- Include authentic design details, materials, colors, plants, street objects, signage, landscape elements, or cultural features that feel appropriate to [CITY], [COUNTRY].- Integrate [LANDMARK_OR_LOCAL_IDENTITY] in a natural and balanced way.- The scene should feel believable, atmospheric, and connected to everyday life or the recognizable character of the place.- Avoid making the landmark feel like a tourist cliché unless the user specifically wants a landmark-focused composition.[COMPOSITION]- Use a clean editorial travel illustration composition.- The illustration may be landscape, portrait, or square depending on the intended use.- Fill the full canvas edge-to-edge.- Do not present the artwork as a printed poster, postcard, card, page, framed print, or paper sheet.- Use balanced negative space for a refined visual feeling.- Place the main visual subject clearly, with supporting local details arranged naturally around it.- Allow open space for typography when appropriate.- Keep the composition clean, readable, and emotionally engaging.[TYPOGRAPHY]- Include the city name “[CITY]” clearly in the image.- Optionally include “[COUNTRY]” in smaller text near the city name.- Use [TYPOGRAPHY_LANGUAGE] for visible typography.- The typography should feel integrated into the illustration itself, not like a random overlay or printed label.- Use tasteful lettering that matches the watercolor-and-ink illustration style.[COLOR PALETTE]- Use a soft, harmonious palette inspired by [CITY], [COUNTRY], and [MOOD].- Favor natural, elegant destination colors.- Colors may include turquoise water tones, soft jungle greens, warm stone neutrals, misty sky blues, earthy browns, and muted tropical foliage accents.- Keep the palette cohesive and refined.[TEXTURE]- Visible watercolor grain inside the painted scene- Transparent paint layering- Soft handmade brush texture- Gentle ink-and-wash finish- Slightly imperfect hand-drawn details- The artwork should feel painted directly across the full image area, not inset inside a page, card, or poster mockup.[MOOD]- The overall mood should feel [MOOD].- Keep the image atmospheric, polished, and emotionally appealing.- The scene should feel like a thoughtful travel illustration rather than a generic tourist poster.[EDGE-TO-EDGE CANVAS RULE]- The illustration must extend fully to all four edges of the image.- Paint, color, and visual elements must reach the top, bottom, left, and right edges.- The final output should look like full-bleed artwork, not a poster placed on paper.- There must be no visible paper sheet, no margin, no mat board, no border, and no white frame.- Do not show the artwork as a printed poster, postcard, card, page, framed print, or mounted artwork.- The canvas itself is the artwork.[RESTRICTIONS]- No photorealism.- No harsh contrast.- No overly saturated colors.- No dramatic cinematic lighting.- Do not overcrowd the composition.- Do not make any single landmark overpower the scene unless requested.- Do not lose the local architectural or environmental identity.- Do not add a white postcard border.- Do not add an outer frame.- Do not create rounded card corners.- Do not leave thick blank margins around the illustration.- Do not place the image on a separate paper sheet or poster mockup.[FINAL INTENT]Create a refined full-bleed watercolor-and-ink architectural travel illustration that captures the character of [CITY], [COUNTRY] through [MAIN_SCENE_TYPE] and [LANDMARK_OR_LOCAL_IDENTITY], using elegant composition, integrated destination typography, soft handmade textures, and an edge-to-edge canvas without any outer frame, white border, postcard margin, or paper-sheet presentation.And on image is english languate only",
        "ExampleImage":  "https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?authuser=0\u0026sz=w800\u0026id=1IH6oDpRh-gyk82z8BY0YBNLdMND8L-Db",
        "Application":  "• สำหรับครูผู้สอน: นำภาพผลลัพธ์ไปประยุกต์ใช้เป็น สื่อกระตุ้นการคิด (Thinking Tools) สื่อประกอบการสอนแบบตั้งคำถาม (Inquiry-based Learning) นำแผ่นภาพโครงสร้างไปทำโมเดลกระดาษสามมิติ หรือทำการ์ดกิจกรรมประกอบแอปพลิเคชันการจัดทำแผนการสอนเพื่อพัฒนาทักษะการวิเคราะห์เชิงลึกของผู้เรียน   • สำหรับผู้บริหาร: ใช้เป็นแนวทางต้นแบบในการส่งเสริมให้ครูผู้สอนพัฒนาสื่อนวัตกรรมการเรียนรู้ที่ทันสมัย สอดคล้องกับแนวคิดนวัตกรรมการศึกษา (Learning Innovation) และสามารถนำสไตล์การจัดสรุปข้อมูล (เช่น โครงสร้าง Infographic หรือพิมพ์เขียว) ไปใช้จัดทำแผนภาพยุทธศาสตร์การพัฒนาคุณภาพของโรงเรียนเพื่อนำเสนอต่อผู้ทรงคุณวุฒิหรือหน่วยงานต้นสังกัด"
